# IDE Control Surface Pack (Walkthrough)

This document summarizes the changes made to implement the **IDE Control Surface Pack** (Option A). This pack transitions the IDE from a personal preference zone to a strictly controlled, normative environment.

## 1. Artifacts Delivered

### A. The Gate: [IDEComplianceChecklist.v1.md](file:///c:/Users/eqhsp/.gemini/antigravity/brain/4d84e3fc-4182-44ee-8105-bdd244f7bb40/IDEComplianceChecklist.v1.md)
*   **What it is:** A normative checklist required for all contributors.
*   **Key Controls:** JSON Schema enforcement, pre-commit hooked, Debugger parity.

### B. The Enforcement: Policy-as-Code Bindings
*   **[.pre-commit-config.yaml](file:///c:/Users/eqhsp/.gemini/antigravity/brain/4d84e3fc-4182-44ee-8105-bdd244f7bb40/.pre-commit-config.yaml):** Enforces trailing whitespace, EOF fixing, and YAML/JSON validity before every commit.
*   **[.editorconfig](file:///c:/Users/eqhsp/.gemini/antigravity/brain/4d84e3fc-4182-44ee-8105-bdd244f7bb40/.editorconfig):** Standardizes indentation (Spaces: 4 for Python, 2 for JSON/Yaml) across all editors.

### C. The Golden Standard: Reference Environment
*   **[.devcontainer/devcontainer.json](file:///c:/Users/eqhsp/.gemini/antigravity/brain/4d84e3fc-4182-44ee-8105-bdd244f7bb40/.devcontainer/devcontainer.json):** A VS Code Dev Container definition.
*   **Guarantee:** Any developer using this container has the **exact** same toolchain (Python 3.10, Docker-in-Docker, Pylance) as CI.

### D. The Process: [CI_PARITY_RUNBOOK.md](file:///c:/Users/eqhsp/.gemini/antigravity/brain/4d84e3fc-4182-44ee-8105-bdd244f7bb40/CI_PARITY_RUNBOOK.md)
*   **Goal:** "If it fails in CI, it MUST fail locally."
*   **Content:** Canonical commands for running the full test suite and debugging in the container.

